node.text: I made a video of how I told Cole  and our friends & family that I was pregnant! I found out in the morning before when we were getting ready for the beach and totally thought the test was going to be negative. I was shocked when it said positive and had Knox run the test out to Cole! I still can’t believe our little family is growing ✨

“ A​ Roadmap To Using Instagram To Grow Your Business”. My passion project I have been working on for months is finally here! This course was created for small business owners, service based brands, and influencers. I wanted to help others follow their dreams and turn their passions into profits! There are 12 Modules covering everything from growth, working with brands, finding a niche, smarter working strategies, launching digital products, and expanding to other social media platforms. These are pantry friendly, kid friendly, refined sugar/ flour free and DELICIOUS! I came up with this recipe a few weeks ago when I needed something to keep us all full on a 10 hour flight. Knox loves them and even got his first little taste of chocolate yesterday because I forgot to to make few without chocolate chips 🙈 Make extra and bring them to family/ friends to let them know you’re thinking of them 💛 Save this post for future reference & share it with a friend! I want to make more recipe videos and next time I’m thinking a dinner meal! Comment what recipes you want to see below 👇🏽 ⁣
*Makes 12 Muffins* ⁣
Ingredients:⁣
- 2 cups oat flour ⁣
- 2 eggs⁣
- 1/3 cup coconut oil ⁣
- 1/3 cup pure maple syrup (or honey) ⁣
- 1 cup mashed bananas⁣
- 1/4 cup milk ( I use almond or oat milk)⁣
- 1 tsp. baking soda⁣
- 1 tsp. Vanilla ⁣
- 1/2 tsp. Sea salt ⁣
- 1 tsp. cinnamon ⁣
- 1/3 cup chopped pecans ⁣
-1/4 cup chocolate chips ⁣
⁣
Directions: ⁣
- Preheat the oven to 325 (162 Celsius)⁣
- Scoop 2 cups of organic oats into a blender. Blend until it is the consistency of flour ⁣
- Mix together all of the ingredients and pour the batter into a greased muffin tin.⁣
- Bake for 20-22 minutes and enjoy!⁣
⁣
Xo, Maddie 
Sound: Bound 2 Instrumental

The perfect blend of sweet, tangy and delicious🌟 My neighbor brought over some fresh lilikoi from her tree and I threw this together! If ya wanna try it out here’s the recipe:
•4 lilikoi (seeds included) • 1 frozen banana (I ran out of frozen ones but it will make the smoothie thicker)
• 1 cup of frozen mango
• 1 cup of frozen peach •1 cup of frozen strawberry • splash of nut milk 
Top with homemade granola, fresh strawberries, banana, more lilikoi, coconut or whatever you’d like! 🍓🥥
We’re also got the product samples in for our shop launching in the New Year 🙌🏽 Any guesses what products from the video we might be releasing?! I am blown away by how this community has grown over the years! This all started while I was a college student trying to create a healthier lifestyle for myself. I never could’ve dreamed I would get the opportunity to connect with all of you from around the world! THANK YOU! I’ll be sending my smoothie ebook to a few of you who comment 💛

node.text: The story of the day our little angel came into the the world 💙

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maddie Castellano on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, baby, people standing, beach and body of water.

node.text: I want my kids to look back on their childhood and remember the days spent under the sun playing at the beach ☀️ I don’t want to hesitate to get messy rolling around in the sand right along with them. We’ve only got 18 summers together, let’s make them count 🥲

node.text:
We are obsessed with this vegan “milkshake” over at our house! Knox goes crazy for this treat and it’s so simple and easy to make. It is full of chocolatey, peanut buttery goodness and will satisfy your sweet tooth. I topped this bowl with my fav @gomacro bar, Double Chocolate + Peanut Butter Chips. They are donating 10% of net proceeds from August sales of this flavor to the Sheldrick Wildlife Trust! These bars are certified Organic, Vegan, Gluten- Free and insanely yummy. We’ve been snacking on these for 5 years now and we’re still in love! ⁣
 ⁣
Recipe: ⁣
2 frozen banana⁣
2 Tbsp raw cacao⁣
2 Tbsp natural peanut butter⁣
1/3 cup almond milk⁣
1 Tbsp chia seeds⁣
Ice

node.text: Boys weekend + mom!! Cole went on a surf trip to Mexico this week so I got to hang with the boys at my parents house in Arizona. Not going to lie, the mom guilt hit HARD the last couple of days. Sometimes I feel like I’ve got it all together and other days I feel like I’m failing. I’ve mostly been feeling really torn about Enzo not wanting to nurse. I breastfed Knox without supplementing for a year and at 6 months Enzo is already wanting to be done. I feel bad that I’m not giving him the same feeding experience as the first baby. Anyone else experience this too?

node.text: I consider myself a professional procrasticleaner🤪 Meaning I will find anything and everything to do before I bring myself do the inevitable cleaning. You already know how much our fam loves @hoover products and I can honestly say that cleaning still sucks, but it sucks a lot less with a good vacuum. Check out my stories for a link to this vacuum that works like a charm and use the code HOOVERPARTNER for 20% off site wide! ⁣
Corn Avocado Salsa:⁣

⁣

We felt completely defeated with our first until a little thing called the Dream Lab came into our life. I will shout my love for the Dream Lab from the rooftops because it gave this mama some much needed sleep! They create a personalized sleep plan for your baby and gives you the tools to help your baby build great sleep habits.
